    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "05206146_e5674787",
        "filename": "ct_pixel_diff/go/ct_pixel_diff/helpers.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-28T14:19:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "These global variables are ok. The alternative is to wrap them in a type and have the handlers be methods of that type. It has made me uneasy in the beginning too, but the trade-off of simple handlers is worth it IMO. BUT they should be kept to the absolute minimum, e.g. \nI don\u0027t think diffStore is used in the handlers, if that\u0027s true, it should not be here, but a local variable in main. \n\nThe globals should also be moved into main, since they are initialized there. \n\nI agree that using the cache this way is not a good approach. The fact that we are caching things should be hidden in the resultStore instance or an intermediate type. \nIt\u0027s not always possible (and done in the Gold code) but the handlers should \n- validate the input \n- call code in resultStore (or another type that contains the \u0027business\u0027 logic)\n- return either an error or the serialized results.",
      "parentUuid": "1d8deeb1_04849b99",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 11
